A chief and four other people on a murder charge were yesterday released on bond. Gakawa chief Lucy Wanja, her assistant and three members of the Nyumba Kumi community policing group are accused of killing a suspected changâ€™aa distiller. They appeared at the High Court in Nanyuki. Justice Mary Kasango ordered each of the five to deposit Sh500,000 bond. The case will be mentioned on February 14. Equator subchief Gertrude Koki, Nyumba Kumi members Loyford Mwirigi, George Wachira and Mary Nyambura were charged on Monday with the murder of Wachira Kabui on October 31 last year in Ichuga village, Nyeri county.